-- Italian Bonds Rise Before Bond Sales With 10-Year Yield at 4.47%
-- B y   L u k a n y o   M n y a n d a   a n d   D a v i d   G o o d m a n
-- 2013-02-13T07:52:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-13/italian-bonds-rise-before-bond-sales-with-10-year-yield-at-4-47-.html
Italian government bonds advanced
for a second day before the nation sells debt.  Yields on the nation’s 5.5 percent debt due November 2022
fell three basis points, or 0.03 percentage point, to 4.48
percent at 7:51 a.m. London time, adding to yesterday’s drop of
11 basis points. Spain’s 10-year rate also decreased by three
basis points, to 5.30 percent.  Italy is scheduled to auction securities maturing between
2015 and 2040 today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lukanyo Mnyanda in Edinburgh at 
